NAF.raw: http : / / www . middevongazette . co . uk / BREAKING - NEWS - Major - supermarket / story - 19548736 - detail / story . html Major fire at supermarket Sunday , July 21 , 2013 FIRE crews from Tiverton and Cullompton were this morning called in to help fight a major blaze at the Waitrose supermarket in Wellington . The fire has destroyed a large section of the store and fire crews and investigators are still on the scene . Two engines were sent to the store after several members of the public called emergency services at 6am . When they arrived they called in an additional six engines , an aerial platform and an incident command vehicle . A corner of the building measuring 50m by 50m containing food was well alight . By 6 . 30am the fire had been contained using water and foam and police had been called . Half an hour later a second aerial platform was called in . and hydrants were being used for extra water . Police advised local residents to shut all doors and windows . Just before 8am crews requested the attendance of an incident support unit from Yeovil for additional drinking water , firefighter welfare and salvage equipment . By 8 . 30am crews were using thermal imaging cameras to identify hotspots and an investigation into the cause of the fire was under way .
